==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|sory|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|sarig|sāriġ|feeling or expressing grief, sorry, grieved, sorrowful, sad, mournful, bitter|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|sairagaz|sad|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|sayǝw-|hard, rough, painful|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{etyl|nds|-}} {{term|serig||sick, scabby|lang=nds}}, {{etyl|de|-}} dialectal {{term|sehrig||sore, sad, painful|lang=de}}. More at {{l|en|sore}}.

